title: Classification of Lipids Structure
body: Lipids can be classified into three (3) categories based on their structure and composition.

title: 3. Derived lipids
body:
Derived lipids are a heterogenous group of biological compounds that are insoluble in water, but soluble in organic solvents. These compounds are referred to as derived lipids because they are formed from simple and complex lipids through the process of hydrolysis. Derived lipids include substances like sterols, prostaglandins, and fat-soluble vitamins.

•  Sterols

•  Prostaglandins

•  Fat-soluble vitamins
